summary: This FBI document details coordination between the FBI's Canberra and Sydney offices, the Australian Federal Police, and the Miami field office to interview a victim of Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell residing in Australia. The interview took place at the U.S. Consulate in Sydney on March 17, 2011, followed by a second interview at the victim's residence to obtain photos.

events.description: A victim of Epstein and Maxwell contacted the United States Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach, Florida, expressing willingness to provide information.

events.title: FBI Interview of Victim in Sydney
events.description: FBI agents conducted an interview of the victim at the U.S. Consulate in Sydney, Australia. Following this, a second interview was conducted at the victim's residence to obtain photos.

locations: Glenning Valley, New South Wales, Australia
keyFacts: A victim of Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell was residing in Australia and willing to provide information to U.S. authorities in March 2011.
The FBI coordinated with the Australian Federal Police to conduct an interview of the victim at the U.S. Consulate in Sydney.
The victim possessed photos at her residence that were deemed pertinent to the investigation, which were obtained by the FBI in a follow-up interview.
The document indicates ongoing international investigative efforts into Epstein and Maxwell's activities years after the initial 2008 plea deal.
